# Running the tests

## Tests based on `webdriver` package

- install chromedriver
- Download selenium-server-standalone-2.53.1.jar from http://docs.seleniumhq.org/download/

Run in a shell:

> java -jar selenium-server-standalone-2.53.1.jar

Run in another shell:

> nix develop .#selenium-example
> cabal test webdriver


## Tests based on `sydtest-webdriver` package

> nix develop .#selenium-example
> cabal run sydtest-webdriver

Notes

- this doesn't work, because sydtest-webdriver uses a wrong version of selenium-server-standalone


